-- Factbox: Recent deals involving cloud-computing companies
-- 
-- Wed Apr 27, 2011 2:03pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/04/27/us-savvis-centurylink-factbox-idUSTRE73Q3RI20110427

 

 (Reuters) - Rural telephone service provider CenturyLink Inc On Wednesday said it agreed to buy Savvis Inc for about $2.5 billion in cash and stock to beef up its data centers business as it looks to meet the growing demand for cloud-based services. 

 Some recent deals involving cloud-based services providers: * No. 2 U.S. cable television provider Time Warner Cable in February bought Navisite Inc a provider of managed applications and services, for $230 million. * Cisco Systems Inc in March said it plans to buy privately held software company newScale Inc, in a deal that would ramp up its cloud computing services. * U.S. phone company Verizon Communications Inc in January bought IT services provider Terremark Worldwide Inc in a deal worth $1.4 billion. * Enterprise data warehousing company Teradata Corp in December agreed to buy privately held Aprimo for $525 million in cash to expand into cloud software services, as it gears up to meet challenges from larger rivals IBM and Oracle. * In November Dell Inc said it will buy U.S. cloud-computing services company Boomi to shore up its ability to provide software over computer networks. (Compiled by Saqib Iqbal Ahmed in Bangalore)